				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Should we do like warriors did?<a name="62983"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 19 04 3:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Think we should have a sit in around the tranq stone in PoK till they respond to some of our issues? just sit there taking up space.
<br />
The issues being: 
<br />
1) either replace our AoE songs or make them more effective in their non-damage compenents as well as increasing their range to our beneficial AOE songs
<br />

<br />
2) giving our melee damage and mitigation an adjustment to be more in line with the other plate classes
<br />

<br />
3) Stop the rehashing of our old songs, give us something original
<br />
(i've both seen and suggested lots of songs that would not be unbalancing)
<br />

<br />
4)  Give us some AA's that are truly bard unique and affect the role of our class.  Personally, i would like to see an AA that would make it so that if several bards with the AA were singing overlapping songs, theyw ould boost each other bit...IE if 2 bards were singing Marr, then all in range could get a 30% boost to its overall effectiveness
<br />

<br />

<br />
As much as i would like to say to have them make us solo better, that just wouldnt fly since there are several classes that cant solo at all ( warrior, rogue, monk, zerker, etc).  But having our dots able to stack would be nice, perhaps getting rid of that d*mn mod cap that we have, maybe an AA that increases the base damage of a our dots.
<br />

<br />
I'm just tired of people B&amp;Ming and doing nothing about it.  You can email every SoE exec out there, they dont care.  They see us playing the game still, they still get your money.  If people cant raid, or at least raid effectively maybe something will get done.</span></td>
