				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, fine, here is my response with some thoughs.
<br />

<br />
1) Ok, ignoring the dmg component for now, the more useful AE songs are Melody of Mischief, AE 45% slow, and Denon's Bereavement, MR debuff. And then there are couple other AE songs with AC debuff, snare. The MR debuff with an average lute is about 40 I belive, and AE slow is 45% slow. They are already pretty good, how much more do you want?
<br />

<br />
2) So you want to tank like warriors/paladins/sks, with your personal haste, slow, sow, fade, mez, charm, kite abilities? If SoE gives that to bards I won't complain. But perpare to see another &quot;warrior sit out&quot; at PoK next time you log on.
<br />

<br />
3) I am netural on this. For what I do solo, group or raid, I find I already have all the tools I want to make things happen. I am not very imaginative on what possible new songs could they make, but I am not a game desginer and not wanting to redesign EQ bard songs. I play with whatever they give me and play it well. Complete new songs? Great, I'll take them and learn how to use them. Re-mix of the old songs? Great, I'll take them and keep on using them.
<br />

<br />
4) No. If there are server bards in the raid, and they don't need to worry about taking different spots to song-cover the whole raid, they should all do different things. i.e. one bard on Marr, one bard on AE resist, one bard on resist debuff etc. Rest of the twist cycles for each bard can be then for group songs.
<br />

<br />
And finally, to thoughfully answer the question &quot;Should we do like warriors did&quot;, no.</span></td>
