				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Should we do like warriors did?<a name="63037"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 19 04 10:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1) Extending the range would be nice.
<br />
2) You obviously dont raid or have no idea about melee combat
<br />
   a)haste means nothing if you have crap for damage tables crap * 60% is stillc crap
<br />
   b)slow, our slow is ok but we still dont mitigate to take too many hits.  i dont think we should mitigate as well as true tanks, but there are silk classes out there that can take a hit better than we can.  That just isnt right.
<br />
  c) our speed.  our speed means nothing in melee combat
<br />
  d) mez, this also means nothing in melee combat, unless of course your talking about meleeing, mezzing, sitting to regen and starting up again.  Well no thanks.  That would take forever to kill one mob, chant kiting is faster
<br />
  e) charm.  This is indirect melee, and if your in the late game and have charm memmed, your a retard (not even going to mention the new charm yet since its effectiving is late game raids has yet to be tested )
<br />
  f) kites.  Our kiting for exp SUCKS.  If i lay down 4 chants plus our minute long dot i 705 damage per tick, thats if there are no resists.  This is also not taking into account the shear number of mobs that snare/cast/summon etc.  It is a much more efficient use of our time to find a group.  But all this is moot since kiting has nothing to do with damage output and mitigation.
<br />

<br />
3) While you may not be able to imagine some new and innovative songs, others have.  Having 5 or 6 songs that do the exact same thing with very similar numbers is just silly.
<br />

<br />
4) It was just an idea.  You do know you can twist songs right?  Most raid bards sing far more than one song on a raid, unless of course your one of those bards that turns on an AE, autofollows the cleric and walks away.  It's thoughts like that that makes bards get marginalized on a raid.
<br />

<br />

<br />
And who ever moved this thread to the rants section, move it back to general, this was not a rant, there are TONS of rants in the general section that do need to be moved.  This was a thread with some constructive ideas, learn how to moderate a forum.
<br />
