			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Should we do like warriors did?<a name="63119"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 20 04 11:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Do I think we should do what the warriors did?
<br />

<br />
No.  It's whiny.  Nothing annoys me like the &quot;I'll hold my breath til I die&quot; kind of threat.  Years ago we got things done by being rational and reasoned.  Maybe that will continue to work if we can actually get peeps to not be whiny and if we can get peeps to not go overboard with trying to power up bards.  
<br />

<br />
As for your concerns:
<br />
1) The only thing that needs addressing is the stacking of the AE's.  
<br />

<br />
I used to be able to stack 4 of them, but now only 2 will stack.  The reason is that 2 of them only have damage components (the level 2 and 18), so they pretty much no longer exist as far as a twist is concerned (because of the new moving rule, since they don't have any other effect to &quot;stack&quot; with, they get ignored).  The functionality needs to be returned to what it was before, as long as we are following the new rule set.  Basically, I spend almost twice as long as I need to be getting thumped by greenies while farming faction.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Extending the range would be nice, but it's not necessary.  
<br />

<br />
2) No one is going to listen to the melee damage complaints because they always bring in stuff that irrelevant and focus on those rather than trying to understand the complaint.  
<br />

<br />
It's pretty simple.  Bards are supposed to be 65% of a similarly equipped warrior for melee damage output given similar equipment.  
<br />
Haste is irrelevant, aa is irrelevant, procs are irrelevant, critter level is irrelevant.  The only factor that's going to make a difference is crits.  Warriors get innate crits and that's going to take them higher for dps.  but you can Factor out the crits (it's a set multiplier isn't it?), and we should be doing 65% of their melee. 
<br />

<br />
As far as mitigation goes, I apparently don't know how it works.  I have an idea how it should work, but my ideas make too much sense and that's not the way it's programmed.  I've just assume that my &quot;plate&quot; armor is about the equivalent of armor made for dinner parties vs armor made for fights.  
<br />
Bards = dinner party armor, everyone else = real armor. 
<br />

<br />
The only thing I'm worried about equipment wise is trying to max out my cha.
<br />

<br />
3) I've been complaining about this since the list was announced.  
<br />

<br />
It all comes down to how easy it is.  It's easier to cut and paste rather than make the songs we have actually scale.  It's also easier to cut and paste rather than make new stuff.  And again, my complaints fall on deaf ears.
<br />
Verant is going to do what's most cost effective, and it's not effective to spend a ton of programmer time on the bard songs.    
<br />

<br />
4) Bard do have some pretty nifty class only aa.  I mean the improved singing and instrument stuff.  Those were a straight up power boost.  When we first got them, it was a straight up 20% + boost across the board.  If we could get Verant to lift the stupid instrument cap, then these aa would actually mean something again.  
<br />

<br />
So, yeah, I want Verant to do 3 things with AA.  
<br />
a) fix the instrument cap, or raise it to a reasonable level that we won't hit for another N expansions (raise it to something like 7 if a number has to be there) 
<br />
b) refund the lame &quot;cap raising&quot; aa and 
<br />
c) give us something useful in it's place.  I'm sure peeps here and at TCH can give ideas (and I have some of my own).  
<br />

<br />
This has the double effect of making the aa we have actually useful, and making the &quot;uber&quot; GoD (and I'm sure OoW) instruments actually mean something again other than stats/hps.  A 3.9 drum and a 3.4 drum should not have the same effect.  
<br />
And it'll be a choice of worn effects and instruments, rather than just worn effects closer and closer to the cap so we don't need instruments at all.  
<br />
(entering dreamland)Do I swap in my 3.9 drum, or do I just keep using my 2.9 rapier?  It should be a choice of 4.7 vs 3.7, not 4.2 vs 3.7. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
