<br />
Listen up, bitchtits.  You're about to get a private audience with the fucking king, so practice your 'thees' and 'thous', wear your best Sunday suit and bring chapstick; you're going to be kissing my browneye until your lips run dry.
<br />

<br />
First off, my little tardling, this was a rant.  This was an angsty, feeble, impotent little zit of a rant that just somehow caught my attention due to the sheer &quot;No, he couldn't mean that fucking retarded sit-in idea, can he?&quot; After the shock wore off that, yes, there are folks that actually think people give a d*mn about a six-year old product on its final stretch before the new kids in the neighborhood give it the final wedgie from above, I sat in comtemplation of your inefficency, and decided that yes, We shall pass Judgement upon thee, and that Judgement is a solid 2.
<br />

<br />
Oh, I could just give you the 1 you deserve, your penchant for ineffective drama is close to He/She/It That Shall Not Be Named, but I'm feeling punchy and after a full day of work, your cute little rant just demanded some offloading of ire.
<br />

<br />
So here we are, sweetcheeks, up front and center with the self-proclaimed, oft ignored, three-hit wonder of the ranting world.  Presented with the opportunity, I wonder, what exactly do you do?  Wet yourself with anticipation?  Stammer unintelligibly?
<br />

<br />
Please.  It's all well and good to argue about the cultural perceptions of classes and how fast you can make the phat loot, but spare me the rhetoric, you want a god class and damnit, you want it now!  And why not?  EQ has shamelessly catered to MUDflation for the past several expansions, that your relative power is certainly much higher than it was, say, at the end of Luclin.  But let's not get too far from the point, sugarnipple.  You're what we call a whiner.  Asking for a bard sit in POK?  What do you think people will say?  They'll never know the difference if someone is playing area mana song, anyway.
<br />

<br />
In conclusion, get off your high horse, hippie.</span></td>
